CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 11, 1941, pg. 14, reads: "Pittsburgh cue-men are doing most of their playing these days at "Woogie" Harris' new, modern billiard parlor. Situated in rear of the new Crystal Barber Shop in the 1400 block on Wiley [Wylie] avenue, this billiard parlor is one of the most modern and completely furnished in the country."
TitMainTitle: Crystal Barber Shop and Billiard Parlor with tin ceiling, hardwood floors, venetian blinds on windows, and wooden chairs lining wall
